3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the problem involves discrete objects (line segments) and their intersections. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) may be relevant as the problem involves finding optimal solutions. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) may be relevant as the paper discusses the time and space complexity of the proposed algorithm.
